<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n05004h"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n05" href="#n05004h">N05 (VI.B.2)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n05all.htm#n05004h"> 4(h)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> bard&apos;s wand <font color="green">[sanctuary]</font></blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">&ldquo;The <mark>Ollamh</mark>, or philosopher,&rdquo; writes Mr. O&apos;Curry, &ldquo;&hellip; was &hellip; entitled to a singular privilege within his territory, that of conferring a temporary <mark>sanctuary</mark> from injury or arrest, by carrying <mark>his wand</mark>, or having it carried, around or over the person or place to be protected. <small> William Bullen Morris, <a name="WBML" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#WBML"><cite title="source">The Life of Saint Patrick Apostle of Ireland</cite></a>, 4th ed. (1890) 163</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
